Switch to kde.  It has several things that can make your computer look like a mac.  Though, nothing will make it operate like one.  For instance, package installation--under the mac it is as simple as drag and drop.  Under linux, well, it's a nightmare.<br />
<br />
KDE is probably your best bet.  Get the baghira from the <a href="http://www.kde-look.org" target="_blank">www.kde-look.org</a> once you have kde set to your active windows manager.<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
